{"id": 20491, "date": "2020-08-16T05:00:00", "date_gmt": "2020-08-16T12:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=20491"}, "modified": "2020-08-15T22:03:29", "modified_gmt": "2020-08-16T05:03:29", "slug": "matr-dion-bruce-springsteen-paul-simon-lou-reed-james-taylor-billy-joel-and-reuben-blades-a-teenager-in-love", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/08/16/matr-dion-bruce-springsteen-paul-simon-lou-reed-james-taylor-billy-joel-and-reuben-blades-a-teenager-in-love/", "title": {"rendered": "MatR: Dion, Bruce Springsteen, Paul Simon, Lou Reed, James Taylor, Billy Joel, and Reuben Blades: A Teenager in Love"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>They weren&#8217;t the Belmonts, but they&#8217;d do in a pinch.</p>\n<p>On the evening of December 13, 1987, Paul Simon organized a benefit concert at Madison Square Garden in order to raise awareness and money to fight homelessness among New York City&#8217;s children.</p>\n<p>The announced line-up was stellar on its own: Simon, of course, along with his Graceland tour mates Ladysmith Black Mambazo; James Taylor, Chaka Khan, Reuben Blades, Dion DiMucci, and Lou Reed were on the bill, too.</p>\n<p>But it was the unadvertised guests during Dion&#8217;s set that sent the crowd through the roof: along with Paul Simon, Lou Reed, James Taylor, and Reuben Blades, Dion surprised the crowd by inviting Billy Joel and Bruce Springsteen to be his honorary Belmonts for the evening.</p>\n<p>Together, the all-star ensemble performed Dion&#8217;s 1959 classic, &#8220;A Teenager in Love.&#8221; (Watch to the end to see Bruce get in one last doo-wop hook.)</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Teenager in love - Dion - homeless benefit concert, 13-12-87\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9hJOwe0vH_s?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>&#8220;A Teenager in Love&#8221; peaked at #5 on the Billboard Hot 100 in 1959. It was one of Dion&#8217;s greatest hits and is almost universally known and loved to this day.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Dion &amp; The Belmonts &quot;A Teenager in Love&quot;\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2pwgswchPDo?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p><strong>A Teenager in Love<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> September 30, 1976 (West Hollywood, CA)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> December 13, 1987 (New York City, NY)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One time only: Bruce Springsteen, Billy Joel, James Taylor, Lou Reed, Reuben Blades, and Paul Simon serve as honorary Belmonts for Dion&#8217;s 1987 benefit performance of &#8220;A Teenager in Love.&#8221;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 20603, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "h